POLOKWANE – “Very warm with sunshine” and “sunny and pleasant” are just some of the conditions expected in Polokwane this week. Warm to hot conditions have been forecast with rain expected over the weekend in the City of Stars. Highs of 32ºC are expected this week, according to AccuWeather’s forecast, with maximum temperatures set to remain in the high twenties and low thirties.  Wednesday (January 11)  will be the warmest day of the week at 32ºC while Sunday will peak at 28ºC. Conditions will remain sunny, with partly cloudy conditions expected over the weekend. There is a 45% chance of rain on Sunday with a 65% chance of cloud cover and 2.5mm of rain expected. Remember to stay hydrated and pack a sun hat for your child as it is back to school this week! 